	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, May 24th 2:57 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=4464><span id=Scholar>arantius, Guardian of the Glade</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>87 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This may technically be an exploit, but I doubt it.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a simple strategy to deal with multiple permarooted mobs.  I learned this strategy watching someone do it for part of coldain ring 9.<br>Have someone be the aggro dummy.  They aggro (very low aggro, perhaps an arrow) all of the permarooted mobs, then SIT DOWN outside of melee range, note that this won't work so well if you have casters blasting your aggro dummy away.<br>Now, the aggro dummy will have permanent aggro on all of those mobs until someone else does something to create more.  Sitting is quite a good chunk of aggro.  Anyways, now your raid force takes out ONE of these targets, while the rest sit there staring stupidly at your aggro dummy, permarooted and unable to get to him.<br><br>Good way to do the crowd control, but everyone there will need to understand what they're doing.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=134066 target=akztarg>Canto Wolfheart</a>, 65th season Druid of Tunare, Quellious server</td></tr>
